name: Landmarks of Dublin
description:
Size: A6 15.5 x 11 cm 

128 pages blank recycled white paper

Handmade in Dublin by a craft bookbindery with the highest care and attention to detail  

Both the cover and paper have a matt finish which is nice to touch.  
There is a red placemarker ribbon. 

 Each notebook is protected by a paper collar.  


The landmarks of beloved Dublin.  Buildings featured are Liberty Hall, The Pigeon Towers at Poolbeg, The Ha'penny Bridge and the central block of Gandon's Four Courts.  There are also some georgian houses but none in particular.

name: Dancers Shopper
